    <div class="full-style">
    <h1>🌍 Find-ISS</h1>

    <p>
        Track the real-time location of the <span class="span-3">International Space Station (ISS)</span> on an interactive Google Map.
        <br>
        This web app fetches live ISS coordinates and displays them with country details.
    </p>

    <h2>🚀 Features</h2>

    <ul class="ul-css">
        <li><span class="span-1"> Live ISS Tracking</span>– Fetch real-time latitude & longitude from the ISS API.</li>
        <li><span class="span-1"> Google Maps Integration</span>– Visualize ISS location on a dynamic map.</li>
        <li><span class="span-1"> Country Detection</span>– Converts coordinates into country names.</li>
        <li><span class="span-1"> Smart Zoom</span>– Adjusts zoom level if ISS is over the ocean.</li>
        <li><span class="span-1"> Auto Refresh</span>– Click a button to update the ISS position.</li>
        <li><span class="span-1"> Secure API Keys</span>– Uses .env to keep keys safe.</li>
    </ul>

    <h2>🛠️ Technologies Used</h2>

    <ul class="ul-css">
        <li><span class="span-2">Node.js & Express.js</span>– Backend framework.</li>
        <li><span class="span-2">EJS</span>– Templating engine.</li>
        <li><span class="span-2">Axios</span>– Fetch external API data.</li>
        <li><span class="span-2">Google Maps API</span>– Display map & markers.</li>
        <li><span class="span-2">dotenv</span>– Secure API keys.</li>
        <li><span class="span-2">CSS & HTML</span>– Styled frontend.</li>
        <li><span class="span-2">Render (Hosting)</span>– Deploy the app online.</li>
    </ul>
